law.text:
The functions of the council shall be to:
Create and update annually a five (5) year management and operational plan to make as effective as possible the coordination, delivery, and marketing of all state environmental education programs;
Establish an interagency subcommittee to advise the council on environmental education matters;
Establish and help coordinate the activities of regional environmental education centers and advisory committees at all state universities and at the central office of the Kentucky Community and Technical College System to serve as networks for the dissemination of environmental education programs, materials, and information across the state;
Establish a competitive system for awarding grants for the establishment and maintenance of regional environmental education centers;
Seek and receive private support to fund state and regional environmental education initiatives;
Assist in the integration and evaluation of environmental education in existing school curricula;
Monitor and report periodically on environmental literacy in Kentucky and continually assess trends and needs in environmental education on a local, state, national, and global basis; and
Make recommendations and seek changes through regulations, legislation, and other means to promote environmental literacy in Kentucky.
